<font color=#ffffff>(9/9/01 3:48:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> EK is generally where I go, mainly because it's easy to reach. I have heard the spiders in Guk are good too. It used to be the spiders in S Ro were a good option too, but I have found once I clear them all, they seem to be on a cycle where they don't come back for a while. You don't really need tracking, you can see spiders a long way off...tag 3-4 with your flux staff and hit them with Jylls, it goes pretty quick. <p><table><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#cc0000 strength=1)><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udiomedes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Diomedes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/20/01 9:20:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> heart spiders in upper guk no contest.<br><br>there are 14 spiders total if memory serves. while crag spiders may drop silks more frequently there are 2 reasons why heart spiders are 100 times better than crag spiders<br><br>1. its a camp - dont need to run around trying to be first to a roamer - dont have to worry about killing mobs on the same spawn table to keep the spawn rotating - you are guaranteed 14 spiders every 15ish minutes.<br><br>2. its a safe camp - sit far back enough in the first &quot;alcove&quot; (where the giant spider spawns) and nothing will aggro you. This means you can go afk between spawns if you want without fear that youll get jumped. Lets face it, farming silk is a seriously boring proposition - you may as well not let that stop you from watching something on TV or doing something else while you wait.<br><br>you can clear all 14 spawns in 3 fights - 10 spawns upstairs, 4 spawns on the &quot;bridge&quot; area - above the water where the skeletal monk for acumen mask spawns.<br><br>IMO anyone who would say that EK is best is trying to keep upper guk a &quot;secret&quot;. Dont be mislead - EK is only better if you have sow and tracking and can stand the tedium of doing something mundane over and over and over again. <p><font face="verdana" size="2">[60 Sorcerer] <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=85843" target="new"><b>Diomedes</b></a></font> (High Elf) <font face="verdana" size="2"><font face="verdana" size="2">&lt;The Vagrants&gt; ZONE:ezboard</font><br><b><font face="verdana" size="2">The Tribunal</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utwiddleotoole.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiddle OToole</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/Twiddle_OToole_bullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/24/01 8:59:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eskimo.com/~aiken/eq/Twiddle_OToole_thumb.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> Yes, but you have to admit it's fun to PBAoE the gnolls by the ramp to Highpass every 10 minutes or so when you're in EK.  I haven't checked, but I may actually not be KoS to the Karana bandits anymore.  Plus you get scalps you can turn in in Highpass for several good factions, including Freeport Militia, if I recall correctly.  I might be thinking of Highkeep goblin ears though.<br><br>I'm a silly person when it comes to faction...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p><table> <tr>  <td style=filter:glow(color=#303870 strength=1)>   <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=5665" style=text-decoration:none><font size=2 color=#6070E0>Twiddle O`Toole</font></a>   <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/bruneofwar35127" style=text-decoration:none><font size=2 color=#6070E0>&lt;Rune of War&gt;</font></a>  </td>  <td valign=bottom>   <font size=1>    &nbsp;  <i>54 <strike>Channeler</strike> Cabbie / Veeshan</i>   </font>  </td> </tr></table><table> <tr>  <td>   <font size=1>    <i>(175 Smith; 168 Researcher; 168 Brewer; 167 Fisherman; 164 Beggar; 148 Potter; 142 Baker; 123 Tailor; 35 Jeweler)</i><br>    <font color=#F00000>Twiddle scowls at you, ready to attack -- what would you like his tombstone to say?</font>   </font>  </td> </tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fredre>Fredre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/23/01 8:52:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> I would have to say EK.  While it does sound like Guk would be better (haven't been there myself), I prefer EK several additional reasons.  One, there are a bunch of lions running around and the HQ pelts can get you to 115 with quivers and the ruined ones can be used to make poison vials (+ pearl + 'chanter friend + silk) can make Wu's armor which get into the upper 140's, IIRC.  Two, there are the occasional HG's that wander about which are good for XP (well at least for me) and cash.  Occasionally you have to clean out the crawlers and hounds, since the number of them seems inversely proportional to the number of lions and spiders.<br><br>Fredre &lt;Adamant Sentinal of Ro&gt; 44th Wizard<br>Druzzil Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usbrobin24.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sbrobin24</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/23/01 7:08:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> &quot;heart spiders in upper guk no contest.&quot;<br><br>I contest.   I tried EK at level 50. I tried guk at 50.  Didn't have enough mana to kill all the spiders in guk until I got that static pulse spell.  I took my 45 necro to EK and there are MUCH more spiders. Sure, you have to run around, but you can get many more silks.   14 spiders every 18 mins is less than the 18 crags I can kill in EK in 18 mins, especially since crags drop more silk. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/6/01 10:55:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's the best place to farm silks?</span><hr size=1> I should add that in EK, if you kill snakes as well as spiders, you'll get more spiders to spawn. They seem to be on the same spawn table.<br><br>- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualurarz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alura RZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/8/01 1:15:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> Using 2 computers, I had a wizard camping at EK, and I had a warrior camped at l guk killing all heart spider spawns.  I'm not sure how long the time was but I reached 8 stacks of spider silk in EK before I reached 6 stacks in l guk, even though 1) I didn't kill all the available spiders in EK, 2) think this is statistically significant.  <br><br>EK Crag spiders just drop alot of spider silks  thank heart spiders.  Of course this changes if there is a druid camping spiders too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyaldin111.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaldin111</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/24/01 1:48:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> Lguk deadly black widows, low 20's spiders, generally get 2 silks off of em but its a linear camp, they're not hard and there's lots of em and it's hardly ever camped.  Got a ton of silks this way.<br><br>Yaldin<br>55 Evoker<br>Karana Server<br>Storm`s Justice <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uobiquon1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obiquon1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/8/02 10:12:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> EK is great, kill spiders (I've had some drop 8 silks) then kill lions (for pelts) while waiting for the spiders to respawn. You can farm here all day.<br><br>Oh, the random HG makes a nice change of pace and gets you a litlle loot.<br> <p><br><br><center><img src="http://www.magicalcheese.com/uploads/obiquon/obisig2.jpg"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68512" target="_blank">[ I got a bad feeling about this ]</a> <br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvespid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vespid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 2:11:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The answer is... EK</span><hr size=1> From my experience:<br><br>53+ wizard:  uguk heart spiders (jylls works wonders)<br>Bard or druid: EK (tracking, sow/selos, pet/melee)<br><br>Your mileage may vary. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showPrevMessage?topicID=98.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showNextMessage?topicID=98.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.emailToFriend?topicID=98.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.threadControl?topicID=98.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=98.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm23.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=98.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=fo